. Executive Consolidation
The Agent Income Estimation Tool is intended to support recruiting conversations by
helping prospective agents and financial professionals estimate potential first-year
commission income using a small set of candidate-facing inputs. The source methodology
explicitly positions the output as a hypothetical estimate, not a guarantee of income. The
estimate is based on historical internal agent performance data, candidate activity
assumptions, and the candidate’s selected client market segment.[]
The logical flow can be separated into five user stories. The first story covers candidate
input capture. The second covers market segment mapping. The third covers income
estimate calculation. The fourth covers results presentation and candidate-facing
sensitivity scenarios. The fifth covers data governance, traceability, assumptions, and
Legal/OGC controls. This structure keeps the requirements aligned to the way a user
experiences the tool while preserving the data and compliance logic needed behind the
scenes.
