US- — Capture Candidate and Activity Inputs
User Story
As a recruiter or prospective candidate, I want to enter a small number of candidate
profile and activity inputs so that the tool can generate a first-year income estimate using a
simple, guided candidate-facing flow.
Description
This story covers the initial intake experience. The tool must collect the fields needed to
identify the candidate, understand the candidate’s intended market, determine
applicable plan or state-specific logic, and capture the candidate’s expected first-year
activity. The intake flow should be concise because the tool is designed for recruiting
conversations and should not require extensive data entry.
The BRD identifies the following inputs: Candidate Name, Working Weeks per Year, Market
Served, Registered Rep, TAS Plan, Appointments Kept per Week, and Candidate State. The
primary estimation-driving inputs are Market Served, Working Weeks per Year, and
Appointments Kept per Week. Other fields support identification, business context,
defaults, state-based availability, or downstream calculations.[]
