US- — Calculate Base First-Year Income Estimate
User Story
As the system, I want to calculate a first-year income estimate from the selected market
segment and activity inputs so that the candidate receives a bounded, historically traceable
income range.
Description
This story covers the core calculation engine. The calculation has two major steps. First, the
selected Market Served determines the candidate’s segment minimum and segment
maximum. Second, the candidate’s activity inputs determine the candidate’s position
within that segment range.
The activity calculation uses Appointments Kept per Week and Working Weeks per Year.
Appointment position is calculated by linear interpolation between benchmark anchor
points. Working weeks are then applied as a proportional scalar, calculated as Working
Weeks divided by . The final activity position is Appointment Position multiplied by the
Working Weeks scalar.[]
