User Story
As a prospective candidate or recruiter, I want to see the estimated income range and
optional scenario adjustments so that I can understand how activity changes may influence
the estimate without confusing those scenarios with guaranteed outcomes.
Description
This story covers the results screen. The BRD states that the output should be shown as a
range, not a single number. It also describes two optional candidate-facing adjustments on
the results screen: Make One More Sale Weekly and % Conversion Increase. These are
not separate primary inputs; they are sensitivity levers shown after the base estimate has
been calculated.[]
The results screen should clearly distinguish the base estimate from sensitivity scenarios.
Because the source document is pending OGC review, the language, placement, and
labeling of these scenario constructs must be controlled carefully before candidate-facing
release.
