. Final Consolidated Acceptance Summary
The solution should be accepted when a recruiter can enter a candidate’s profile and
activity assumptions, select the intended market, generate a historically bounded first-year
income range, optionally view clearly labeled post-calculation scenarios, and provide the
candidate with a compliant explanation that the estimate is hypothetical. The underlying
system must preserve the approved segment ranges, calculation formulas, data population
assumptions, and OGC review status so that every displayed value is explainable and
auditable.

